EventText1 = "You have heard about our research on the mineral Murt. We have made progress lately. We only have very small quantities of the mineral. If we manage to find greater amounts, it would really help the sector."#"On the other hand, it could also be used for creating almost unimaginably powerful weapons, shields and bombs."#"We have reasons to believe that there is a huge source of Murt somewhere in this sector."#"We think the the rebels know about this."#"If they gained access to it, it would be a catastrophe."#"We must stop them at all costs."#"It is here you come in. We need an insider. Someone they can trust, who can provide us with insight into what they know and what they plan."#"You are a skilled and trusted pilot and you are unknown to them."#"Sometimes people leave the Alliance and join the rebels, fooled by their nice words. You could pretend to be one of them."#"Our plan is to let you leak crucial information to them about a coming attack against one of their outposts near Lavis."#"You will join them during the attack. You will be sent there together with a group of suspected traitors."#"You and the rebels will help us get rid of them."#"I have set up a meeting with a lower rebel leader at coordinates (-145, 2300)."#"You should travel there immediately, and hand him this information."#"Then, you will travel to the outpost and join the attack fleet. I will provide you with the exact coordinates after the meeting."#She looks at you seriously.#"Good luck. I will stay in touch."
EventText2 = [SAIR] "That was unexpected. But it might be the logical choice. Let‚Äôs go meet that rebel person."
EventText3 = [SAIR] "You know, this might be the last moment of stillness we get in a while."#"You should take a moment to appreciate it."
EventText4 = A young man with a fierce look appears on your display.#[Rok] "So you came after all. And you seem to have no company. Brave!‚Äù#"Stupid, but brave.. Let‚Äôs get to it. You had information. Send it over."#He speaks with a quite harsh voice. He doesn't seem as confident with the situation as he tries to appear.#You transfer the information.#[Rok] "..."#"... Why would you tell us this. A change of heart you say?"#"..."#"I will leave you now. If this is true, and you follow the plan through, there will be a place for you among us."#"If not... I will make sure you regret this meeting."#"Goodbye for now."#The screen goes blank, and the small group leaves silently.
EventText5 = [SAIR] "That was tense. It wouldn't have been illogical for them to shoot us down at the spot."
EventText6 = [Ai] "..Did it go as planned? Good. Now, join the attack fleet at coordinates (1235, 1400)."#"There is no looking back now. This might be our best chance to get a grip on the rebels."
EventText7 = [SAIR] "Remember. Even if the Alliance fleet we will join consists of quite unexperienced pilots, they will have better equipment than most of the rebels we have faced this far."#"Be careful."
EventText8 = A rough and seemingly annoyed man appears on your display.#[Attack fleet leader] "You are late, scum. What do you think this is? A walk in the park?"#"I will not watch your back if you not are able to follow orders."#He directs his next message to the entire fleet.#"I will not hold a fucking inspirational speech for you. Do your job, and we can go home."#"I don't know what they are fucking thinking, sending us here. I guess someone has to do their dirty job."#"Let‚Äôs try to make this as quick as possible. Go in, destroy everything, and leave."#"Make sure they don't have time to forward the message, or we will be swarmed by their ships on our way back."#"Let's move out. Don‚Äôt fall behind."
